# SQL 
  - Structured Query Language
  - Standard querying langauge used everywhere
  - For example: MySQL, PostgreSQL



# T-SQL
  - Transact SQL
  - It is an extension of SQL
  - SQL + Programming features (loops, conditions, variables)
  - Used in Microsoft SQL server
  - We can use vairables, error hannding, if else


for example VARIABLES:

DECLARE @threshold INT = 10000;

SELECT State, SUM(Total) AS total
FROM suicidesindia_2001_2012
GROUP BY State
HAVING SUM(Total) > @threshold;
